According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global Cobalt Recycling Market was valued at USD 1,443 million in 2024 and is projected to grow from USD 1,587 million in 2025 to USD 3,479 million by 2032, registering a robust CAGR of 13.7% during the forecast period.
The market is witnessing rapid expansion as industries increasingly prioritize sustainable resource management and secure supply chains for critical battery materials. Cobalt recycling has become an essential component of the circular economy by recovering valuable cobalt from end-of-life lithium-ion batteries, industrial scrap, and cobalt-containing alloys. The growing adoption of electric vehicles (EVs), rising environmental concerns, and corporate commitments to responsible sourcing are accelerating investments in advanced recycling technologies worldwide.
